    <stitle>7.3 Liter Diesel Engine Service (1991) - VALVE TRAIN: CAMSHAFT, HYDRAULIC VALVE LIFTERS AND PUSH RODS -
        CAMSHAFT ASSEMBLY
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>CAMSHAFT ASSEMBLY</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="proctype" graphiccount="1">
            <title>NEW CAMSHAFT ASSEMBLY BALANCE</title>
            <para>Improved camshaft assembly balance is achieved by the addition of a counterweight lug to the inboard
                side of the cam gear, as well as elimination of the drilled &#38; tapped gear puller bosses. Refer to
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef4350407">4.7</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                .
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Gear puller holes and related bosses were eliminated to facilitate machining and camshaft
                        assembly balance. Cam gear removal is now accomplished using any common three jaw pressure screw
                        puller.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <figure id="ef4350407" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="cg14738" filename="../figcg1/CG14738.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 4.7 Cam Gear Comparison [Weighted vs. Unweighted]</caption>
            </figure>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
